{
  "texts": [
    "Who pays and who receives is a frequent point of litigation.",
    "The European Parliament's amendments to the proposed AI Act aim to provide extensive privileges to free and open-source AI components.",
    "Recital 12a states: ''To foster the development and deployment of AI, especially by SMEs, start-ups, academic research but also by individuals, this Regulation should not apply to such free and open-source AI components except to the extent that they are placed on the market or put into service by a provider as part of a high-risk AI system or of an AI system that falls under Title II or IV of this Regulation.''",
    "The wording is implemented under a new Art. 5(d).",
    "As with Art."
  ]
}